>> # Diabetes UK in the North of England
>> ### The North of England team is a network of staff, volunteers and
healthcare professionals leading the fight against the fasting growing health
>> With over 930,000 people diagnosed with diabetes in the north of England
and thousands more at risk of developing Type 2 diabetes, our work in
supporting people affected by the condition and helping to improve the care
>> Our work to improve care and outcomes for people living with diabetes
stretches across the region, and includes campaigning, sharing good practice,
>> We do not provide clinical care, however we work with the NHS across the
north of England to help improve care and outcomes for people living with
diabetes. We do this through campaigning, sharing good practice, raising
awareness, fundraising and funding research in the region.
>> Our work wouldn’t be possible without the support of our volunteers and the
local groups scattered across the region supporting local people with the
condition, giving information to people newly diagnosed and also keeping up to
date with diabetes care through talks from diabetes specialists.
>> In addition we have a team of locally based regional fundraisers who
support the incredible fundraising efforts of our many local supporters,
specialist guidance on how to make the most their fundraising activities.
